      "acceptanceCriteria": "Verification tests confirm solver correctly implements governing equations; achieved level meets required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark verification cases (lid-driven cavity, Poiseuille flow) were executed and results matched analytical solutions within accepted tolerances, confirming correct numerical implementation of the Navier-Stokes equations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study performed with GCI < 5%; achieved level meets required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the scalar stress index was below 4.2%, confirming adequate spatial resolution at the selected mesh density of 8.4 million elements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions are documented and reproducible; achieved level meets required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions (flow rate 2.5 L/min, rotational speed 2500 RPM, working fluid viscosity and density characterised) are fully documented in published FDA reports and were faithfully reproduced in the simulation boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) computed and within acceptable range; achieved level meets required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted pressure rise and velocity profiles were compared against FDA PIV and pressure measurements. Mean absolute error in pressure rise was 3.1% and velocity field agreement was within one standard deviation of experimental uncertainty across all measurement planes."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
