      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to hemolysis prediction and worst-case identification; achieved level meets required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the scalar stress index (SSI) and derived hemolysis index (HI), which are directly used by the decision maker to rank operating conditions by hemolysis risk. These QoIs are established in the hemolysis modelling literature and are appropriate for the intended ranking decision."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
